n 415. His speeches are a defense against charges relating to those events.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aOratory, Ancient. 0aSpeeches, addresses, etc., GreekvTranslations into English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aGagarin, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGagarin, Michael.1 aMacDowell, Douglas M.1 aMacDowell, Douglas M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292799110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292799110/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK